WEBVTT

00:00:00.100 --> 00:00:03.987
The Truth About Learning A Brief Lesson in Language 1

00:00:04.200 --> 00:00:08.150
All knowledge we acquire can be described using language 2

00:00:08.300 --> 00:00:12.238
Humans can pass on knowledge through language and writing 3

00:00:12.412 --> 00:00:15.412
The purpose of language is to describe and convey perception

00:00:16.300 --> 00:00:19.475
4 The elements of language are objects nouns and verbs

00:00:19.637 --> 00:00:24.337
and perception adjectives and adverbs 5 The function of various

00:00:24.350 --> 00:00:29.363
vocabulary 1 Nouns record things you can perceive whether abstract

00:00:29.387 --> 00:00:33.975
or concrete 2 Verbs record actions you can perceive whether

00:00:33.987 --> 00:00:38.600
active or passive 3 Adjectives record your perception of things

00:00:38.625 --> 00:00:42.763
you can perceive 4 Adverbs modify verbs to record your

00:00:42.788 --> 00:00:45.875
perception of actions you can perceive or modify adjectives to

00:00:45.900 --> 00:00:48.337
record your perception of your perception of things you can

00:00:48.350 --> 00:00:53.013
perceive 6 Language can be divided into two types natural

00:00:53.038 --> 00:00:58.475
language and artificial language 7 Artificial language uses limited clear

00:00:58.650 --> 00:01:03.825
and unambiguous vocabulary 8 Artificial language is a simplified version

00:01:03.850 --> 00:01:09.688
of natural language unambiguous nouns unambiguous verbs and determiners 9

00:01:09.888 --> 00:01:13.475
Scientific knowledge is expressed using artificial language which is a

00:01:13.487 --> 00:01:15.075
simplified version of language

